Vice President Pence, along with Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross and Secretary of Interior David Bernhardt, visited Artesia, New Mexico to discuss the importance of the Permian Basin in the American energy renaissance. They called on the people of New Mexico to support the passage of the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and urged their elected representatives to bring it to the floor for a vote. Pence also addressed the recent mass shootings in El Paso and Dayton, stating that the administration is exploring legislation to prevent such incidents and emphasizing the need for mental health support and vigorous law enforcement. He also discussed a new rule allowing indefinite detention of migrants and efforts to improve conditions in facilities. Pence highlighted the benefits of the USMCA for American workers and the economy, and expressed the administration's commitment to winning over voters in New Mexico in the upcoming election.